    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "We had on the Send transaction view (when sending from Wallet) ‘You are on [network]. [Real/Test] ETH will be sent’. But then we introduced new tx flow and lost it (we have those actually now too but just when sending from Wallet)\r\nThe same in my opinion would make sense to reflect in the ‘Sending transaction’ bottom sheet, i.e. displaying network in all cases.\r\n\r\nRisks here are about what is going on to be sent: mainnet or testnet assets. \r\n\r\nThe worst case that may happen is that user sends real ETH thinking (s)he send test ETH.\r\nSo to mitigate this risk when on TestNet we should display `TestNet` label. \r\nBut when on Mainnet, we alarm user with `Mainnet` label: \"Beware, you are on Mainnet, you operate with real ETH!\" \r\n \r\n\r\n> risk of mistaking testnet for mainnet, to be in sending funds to a testnet address, not from a testnet address.\r\n\r\nTestnet address is the same as Mainnet address for one account. And when scanning QR code of address there is even network_id inside which will notify sender about different network.  \r\n\r\nSo if we decide to have network value indication in `Sending...` bottom sheet, my call if to display network value disregard its testnet or mainnet. \r\n",
