    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "> The worst case that may happen is that user sends real ETH thinking (s)he send test ETH.\r\nGot it, so you might send a high amount on Mainnet, mistaking it for Testnet.\r\n\r\nIf that's the risk I suspect the currency indicator (ETHri ETHro STT) plays an important role in communicating what you're sending. This hasn't always been that visual, if we even use a distinction at all. We can also play with absence presence of USD value. E.g. show USD on Mainnet, and replace it with something like Test token on Testnet. @andmironov this could be an alternative to hidden fields you mentioned above. It can be hard to notice the difference in something that's not there witout a side-by-side comparison.\r\n\r\n\r\n> So if we decide to have network value indication in Sending... bottom sheet, my call if to display network value disregard its testnet or mainnet.\r\n@Serhy can you elaborate what you mean with `network value`?\r\n",
